   Let me explain Rust's ownership model.

  ┌─ thinking
    I should cover the three rules:

    1. Each value has one owner
    2. Only one owner at a time
    3. Value dropped when owner goes out of scope

   The key insight is that ownership prevents data races at compile time.
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
